Two officers of the Nigerian Air Force have tested positive for COVID-19 in Makurdi, Benue State. Governor Samuel Ortom made the disclosure during a broadcast on COVID-19 in the state on Wednesday. To curtail a further spread of Coronavirus in the state, Ortom said he had directed the wider processes to trace, isolate and test all primary and secondary contacts with the cases especially the NAF base located along the Makurdi/Gboko Road. The governor also announced the lifting of the ban on worship centres and the resumption of work by all civil servants with effect from Monday, June 8.